      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your feelings of being fundamentally broken are valid, but they are understandable symptoms of an immense, crushing load rather than an inherent flaw in your character. When the noise feels persistent and the future seems impossible, it is natural to feel overwhelmed by the pressure to simply stop everything. Please consider that seeking professional support for a therapist or counselor can provide a safe space to processor these intense emotions with someone who understands the depth of your struggle.",
      "source": "target",
