      "content": "I hear that you are exhausted from being told to just \"hang in there\" when your pain feels physical and total, and it is completely understandable to feel that only the darkness offers a logical escape from such ruin. Please know that while your desire to stop hurting is valid, the idea that letting go is the only solution ignores the possibility that survival—even in pain—allows you to eventually find a different kind of peace that isn't just the absence of feeling. If the weight feels too heavy to carry alone, consider reaching out to a crisis line where you can speak without judgment or platitudes, as there are people who want to listen to the very real horror you are describing.",
